# * --period-titles option

# ** 1. compact headings are the default, describing subperiods in compact form when feasible
# (eg falling on natural period boundaries, and within a single year).
<
2024/1/1
  (a)  1
2024/2/1
  (a)  1
$ hledger -f- balance --monthly
Balance changes in 2024-01-01..2024-02-29:

   || Jan  Feb 
===++==========
 a ||   1    1 
---++----------
   ||   1    1 

# ** 2. --period-titles=dates always shows full ISO dates or date ranges.
<
2024/1/1
  (a)  1
2024/2/1
  (a)  1
$ hledger -f- balance --monthly --period-titles=dates
Balance changes in 2024-01-01..2024-02-29:

   || 2024-01-01..2024-01-31  2024-02-01..2024-02-29 
===++================================================
 a ||                      1                       1 
---++------------------------------------------------
   ||                      1                       1 

# ** 3. --period-titles=dates affects other output formats, like csv.
<
2024/1/1
  (a)  1
$ hledger -f- balance --monthly -O csv --period-titles=dates
"account","2024-01-01..2024-01-31"
"a","1"
"Total:","1"

# ** 4. An invalid argument gives a helpful error message
<
2024/1/1
  (a)  1
$ hledger -f- balance --monthly --period-titles=foo
>2 /--period-titles's argument should be "compact" or "dates", not "foo"/
>=1
